    "actions_taken": [
      "Mud Logger notified Driller of 1 barrel loss in trip tank",
      "Driller turned pump to trip tank off",
      "Crew engaged lower TJ seal to stop SBM discharge",
      "Operator notified BSEE and National Response Center (NRC)",
      "BSEE inspectors arrived on location 22 June 2015 to investigate"
    ],
    "summary": "On 20 June 2015, a 12 barrel discharge of Synthetic Base Mud (SBM) at 11.3 ppg occurred on the Ensco 8500 drilling rig during drill pipe extraction. The upper riser telescopic joint (TJ) seal failed, allowing SBM to discharge into offshore waters. The audible alarm for the TJ seal did not sound because air pressure remained within the normal operating range of 100 psi. The crew detected the visible leak and engaged the lower TJ seal to stop the discharge.",
